issue_body:
If the sub-statements of a type are not in canonical order, as well as generating "not in canonical order" errors pyang generates "circular dependency for type" errors which don't make sense. For example, the following Yang:
typedef threshold-event-enum {
    description
      "Enumeration of the valid threshold event types";
    reference	
      "[802.3] 57.5.3";
    type enumeration {
    ...

Produces the following errors:
experimental/ieee/802.3/ethernet-link-oam.yang:80: error: circular dependency for type "threshold-event-enum"
experimental/ieee/802.3/ethernet-link-oam.yang:82: error: keyword "description" not in canonical order, expected "type", (See RFC 6020, Section 12)

